                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful, irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of 19th century and first half of the 20th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor; incipit of Text I;
                           on the incipit page of Text I (fol. 3r) and on fol. 63r, a few lines are
                           rubricated (alternating with black lines); titles, initial lines or
                           initial word of the prayers to be read; directives to the ministers;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numbers.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Careful and neat on the initial fols.,
                        the handwriting deteriorates and becomes irregular and
                        uneven.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week crudely written in the upper margin in a secondary
                              hand in pencil: ዘሰኑይ: <locus target="#3r">fol. 3r</locus>. ዘሠሉስ:
                                 <locus target="#13v">fol. 13v</locus>. ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#25r">fol. 25r</locus>. ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#35r">fol. 35r</locus>.
                              ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#47r">fol. 47r</locus>. ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#54v">fol. 54v</locus>. ዘእሁድ: <locus target="#63r">fol.
                                 63r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Pen trials: fols. 1r, 1v, 2r, 2v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
